SECURITY IN WEB APPS

Web apps can be secured using authentication and authorization, tokens and JWT comes into picture.


AUTHENTICATION

(1) means making sure that a person or device is who (or what) they claim to be.
(2) ensures that data is not exposed to the wrong person.
(3) common methods: username and password combination, multi-factor authn, public key certificate, biometric authn


AUTHORIZATION

(1) determines what an authenticated user can see and do.
(2) same as 'permissions'


OPEN AUTHORIZATION (OAUTH)

(1) standard for passing authz from one service to another. 
(2) used for cloud services
(3) Without the use of OAuth, a user's permissions would have to be set up separately in each application.